race.comment: Onto the Pakenham Cup and all eyes will be on the start with SKIPPERS CANYON (16), who missed the kick badly at Caulfield second up as $3 favourite, running on very well but a forlorn hope from so far back. No doubt the ability is there and 2500m looks ideal with 54kg, if he jumps cleanly he'll go close. BLACK RUN (11) is flying having won his past three. They haven't been by big margins but he's been doing enough and puts himself in the right spots which will be key. ZIRYAB (15) was beaten a nose by BLACK RUN last time out and drops 6kg from that. His form over this sort of trip is good and he lands in a great spot from the draw. ALENQUER (2) tried hard in the G2 Zipping Classic last time when pushing forward and looming as a chance at big odds, finishing fourth. This is easier and he looks a decent each-way proposition. ETNA ROSSO (3) is racing well and went past ALENQUER last time, he just looks to get a mile back from the wide gate.
